Basic Commands:

#whoami     -->display current user
#pwd           -->display present working directory
#hostname  -->shows hostname/machiname
#hostaname   <name>  --> change hostname
->#bash      -->update changes
#uname -a      -->display os information
#cat /etc/os-release      -->display os info
#date          --> display current date
#date  -s  '2024-04-16 10:15:05'  -->change date
#<command>  --help    -->it will display all options related to command
#man  <command>       -->complete info about commmand
#whatis  <command>    -->short info about command
#ls               -->list all files and directories
#cd             -->change directory (get inside directory)
	 ls   -a         -->list hidden files
	 ls   -l          -->long list, it will list detaied info of files
	  ll               -->long list
	 cd             -->change directory (get inside directory)
	 cd  ..        -->back to previous location
	 free  -h   -->display free memory
	 df  -h       -->display disk details(storage)
	 du  -sh    -->display size of file or directory
	 dmidecode    -->display hardware information
	sudo -i                  -->switch to root user
	su root                 -->switch to root user
	sudo - root           -->switch to root user
	su - username      -->switch to local user
	exit                       -->logout from current user

